          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Part D Beneficiary Appeals Fairness Act</b></p> <p> Amends part D (Voluntary Prescription Drug Benefit Program) of title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act, with respect to a prescription drug plan (PDP) that provides for any tiered cost-sharing within a formulary (including a structure that provides for different co-payment or coinsurance amounts for drugs in different tiers included within the formulary), to authorize a Medicare part D eligible individual enrolled in the plan to request an exception to the tiered cost-sharing structure.</p> <p>States that in no case may the Secretary of Health and Human Services allow a PDP sponsor to make any formulary tier of the tiered cost-sharing structure (including a formulary tier used for very high cost or unique items) ineligible for lower-cost sharing through an exception.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDate>2015-06-03</actionDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-06-29T19:25:51Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
